cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the problem of transparent object pose estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves robotics and manipulation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning and generative sampling techniques indicates that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the use of light-field sensing and photorealistic rendering, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
